column11: SOPHIE was pretty easy to use - it was nice to have the intro to her before using her so I knew what to expect.
column27: SOPHIE's voice could have been more human-like and she could have sounded less monotone. Furthermore, she could have used more body language.
column38: Overall, the feedback was straightforward and helpful.

column11: SOPHIE was very easy to use
column27: SOPHIE overall felt like a realistic experience.
column34: I was shocked by how well SOPHIE responded to what I said
She didn’t allow me to finish a sentence

column11: Note for the first time that the microphone indicates when Sophie is “listening”. Being able to see the notes on the patient and treatment options would be helpful, just as having chart notes on hand in a real appt.
column27: For the version I interacted with today,  the face stayed amongst exactly the same and the voice had little inflection. There was one time when her pitch dropped and her pace slowed which I read as some emotional change. If th ere are already modulations to her cadence, then perhaps I got “depressed” Sophie today?
column34: When I fumbled my own speech and said “stay out of pain” it felt weird to hear that mirrored back to me with those exact words. Her way of starting nearly every turn with thank you, doctor, also seemed less realistic.
column38: I liked the way it is structured. It was easy to get to what I needed and to see exactly what I said. I also enjoyed the rating scales like good/fast for speaking rate.
column45: The direct examples that are shared are great resources especially for a med student
column54: I especially like the feedback in pace and reading level. And I needed the tips on communicating directly.
column64: I especially enjoyed seeing the distribution of talking time. This will be a very powerful tool. May I please use that in some board meetings??

column27: While her natural talking voice sounded more human and less AI than expected, there could be improvement to her changing her voice to match/express different emotions especially more deeper emotions like anger, fear or sadness.
column34: Her sentences were almost to perfect English, most humans especially when upset would be completely proper.

column11: Sophie was very user friendly and straightforward!
column27: I was able to feel empathy for Sophie too!
column34: I think some of her responses were a bit general and were not specific to the case.
column38: I really loved how detailed the feedback was!
column45: I loved the suggestions for improvement!
column54: I loved that the hedge words, speaking rate, and reading level was calculated. I also liked that the amount of (open-ended) questions was included in the analysis.
column64: I loved that the amount of questions was calculated. I did not realize that I asked so few!

column34: Quite honestly, I think she was reassured too fast/trusted the doctor too easily

column27: Sadness wasn't super easy to pick up with SOPHIE, but frustration and concern were easier to pick up and recognize in my opinion.
column38: I thought it was easy to understand and digest, not too much to be overwhelming

column34: She did repeat a similar question multiple times during the Explicit module.

column11: SOPHIE was relatively easy to use. It took a bit of time to get used to the AI, but after a few minutes I believe I worked diligently and efficiently.
column27: SOPHIE can definitely become more human-like over time, but as early as they are in the AI stage, SOPHIE still provides an adequate representation of a human patient.

column11: Iiyt was all spoon fed to me. So It seemed easy to use.
column27: I thought Sophie needed greater expressions. Mostly she was stiff, with occasional facial emotions.
column34: Occasionally there was repetitiveness. Also a false thank you for being a good listener.
column38: I found the feedback useful. Both positive and "needs improvement"
column54: I liked the hedge words. I don't know whether speaking rate useful in and of itself, other than don't talk too fast
column64: I think this may have been the section I got zero good feedback, even though I thought I did some things OK.

column27: To me it just didn’t seem genuine enough, maybe it was because I knew it was Ai and not a actual person.
